WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:14.160 --> 00:00:18.670
One Piece One Piece

3
00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:19.420
Wano Arc Wano Arc Wano Arc

4
00:00:18.670 --> 00:00:19.420
One Piece

5
00:01:41.870 --> 00:01:44.330
Oh, Inuarashi!

6
00:01:44.810 --> 00:01:46.830
Where have you been?

7
00:01:46.830 --> 00:01:48.920
Something wrong, Kin'emon?

8
00:01:49.620 --> 00:01:51.670
We're in a real predicament!

9
00:01:50.090 --> 00:01:53.420
<b>Kin'emon and
the Mink Musketeers
An Abandoned Village
Kuri</b>

10
00:01:54.030 --> 00:01:58.050
The enemy knows about
the flyer and the moon tattoo?!

11
00:01:58.050 --> 00:02:01.300
That's right! It's all a big mess!

12
00:02:01.300 --> 00:02:03.890
What do we do, Your Grace?!

13
00:02:04.570 --> 00:02:07.700
We were distributing these covertly...

14
00:02:07.700 --> 00:02:10.860
I do not know how it leaked...

15
00:02:10.860 --> 00:02:16.820
We chose this coded symbol on
the off chance it fell into the wrong hands.

16
00:02:16.820 --> 00:02:24.170
But they've somehow uncovered
the connection between this and the tattoo.

17
00:02:26.160 --> 00:02:27.750
Right now in the capital...

18
00:02:27.750 --> 00:02:33.170
Kaido and Orochi's underlings
are apprehending our allies!

19
00:02:27.870 --> 00:02:33.170
<b>A Woman's Secret</b>

20
00:02:34.710 --> 00:02:37.460
– You're under arrest!
– You're under arrest!

21
00:02:39.570 --> 00:02:43.140
Stop resisting, rebel scum!

22
00:02:43.560 --> 00:02:46.100
He had a flyer on him!

23
00:02:47.760 --> 00:02:50.350
Settle down!

24
00:02:50.350 --> 00:02:52.810
He's got the moon tattoo, too!

25
00:02:53.660 --> 00:02:57.110
Anyone with that mark
on their ankle is a rebel!

26
00:02:57.870 --> 00:03:00.050
Report any you see!

27
00:03:05.500 --> 00:03:07.670
Word travels fast.

28
00:03:07.670 --> 00:03:10.500
The entire capital will have heard by now.

29
00:03:10.500 --> 00:03:14.480
Patrolling bathhouses is
just going to waste our time.

30
00:03:15.210 --> 00:03:17.470
How fortunate for you.

31
00:03:17.470 --> 00:03:19.090
What's that supposed to mean?

32
00:03:25.160 --> 00:03:28.470
That's Stealth Black for you...!

33
00:03:28.470 --> 00:03:30.140
I'll get him next time!

34
00:03:30.690 --> 00:03:33.990
You're just as culpable
for letting them escape.

35
00:03:39.070 --> 00:03:42.030
Oh, Komurasaki...!

36
00:03:55.000 --> 00:03:57.380
Boss Kyoshiro...

37
00:03:57.960 --> 00:04:01.260
Komurasaki's wake has been canceled.

38
00:04:01.260 --> 00:04:06.470
Things might get out of hand
if this many grief-stricken people pour in.

39
00:04:02.260 --> 00:04:02.930
<b>A Pleasure Hall

Flower Capital</b>

40
00:04:02.930 --> 00:04:07.970
<b>A Pleasure Hall

Flower Capital</b>

41
00:04:07.970 --> 00:04:12.680
The funeral tomorrow will
probably be even more crowded.

42
00:04:13.580 --> 00:04:16.520
May she rest in peace!

43
00:04:16.520 --> 00:04:21.270
Many are placing the blame
for this upon your shoulders...

44
00:04:21.940 --> 00:04:23.650
Please be careful.

45
00:04:24.720 --> 00:04:27.200
They should mind their own business.

46
00:04:32.370 --> 00:04:36.580
There was no other way...

47
00:04:36.580 --> 00:04:40.580
The one with the most to lose...

48
00:04:40.580 --> 00:04:41.960
is me.

49
00:04:42.720 --> 00:04:44.250
Certainly.

50
00:04:50.260 --> 00:04:54.370
Lord Orochi is still in a foul mood.

51
00:04:54.370 --> 00:04:58.140
I'd wager this is the thorn in his side.

52
00:05:06.530 --> 00:05:13.080
<b>Ebisu Town</b>

53
00:05:06.900 --> 00:05:08.900
Stop it, you two!

54
00:05:08.900 --> 00:05:11.870
Arguing won't resolve any of this!

55
00:05:13.080 --> 00:05:15.000
We're on the same side!

56
00:05:17.250 --> 00:05:21.820
They're arresting everyone who sympathizes 
with our goal of eliminating Orochi...

57
00:05:23.000 --> 00:05:26.180
ever since your crew slipped up!

58
00:05:26.990 --> 00:05:28.060
What was that?!

59
00:05:28.060 --> 00:05:30.640
That little bear and his pals...

60
00:05:30.640 --> 00:05:33.970
must have told them the plan!

61
00:05:35.180 --> 00:05:40.690
Bepo and the others would rather die
than talk! Don't underestimate them!

62
00:05:41.760 --> 00:05:45.310
Wait! You're doing exactly
what the enemy wants, Traf!

63
00:05:45.310 --> 00:05:49.200
Don't you tell me what to do, Black Leg!

64
00:05:49.200 --> 00:05:52.410
Both of you, simmer down.

65
00:05:53.120 --> 00:05:56.740
You're the one who needs to cool your head!

66
00:05:57.710 --> 00:05:59.260
You have to...

67
00:05:59.260 --> 00:06:01.860
You have to trust each other!

68
00:06:01.860 --> 00:06:04.580
You're the most untrustworthy person I know!

69
00:06:08.850 --> 00:06:11.270
I didn't see a thing...

70
00:06:11.270 --> 00:06:15.270
How'd your face end up like
that after a few punches...?

71
00:06:16.820 --> 00:06:17.940
Are you trying to run?!

72
00:06:17.940 --> 00:06:21.600
We need to eliminate those
who were captured!

73
00:06:22.110 --> 00:06:23.400
They must be silenced!

74
00:06:23.400 --> 00:06:24.770
What did you say?!

75
00:06:24.770 --> 00:06:27.510
That is the way of the ninja world!

76
00:06:27.510 --> 00:06:29.680
You're scary, Shinobu!

77
00:06:33.290 --> 00:06:36.420
This isn't some game we're playing!

78
00:06:41.810 --> 00:06:46.010
We've been waiting
twenty years for this moment!

79
00:06:46.010 --> 00:06:50.420
If we fail, we won't get another chance!

80
00:06:54.630 --> 00:06:57.090
That's enough, Shinobu!

81
00:06:58.610 --> 00:07:00.320
Kan! My lord!

82
00:07:02.160 --> 00:07:04.900
Things do not always go as planned!

83
00:07:04.900 --> 00:07:07.100
I understand your frustration well...

84
00:07:07.100 --> 00:07:12.870
but it's a miracle we found allies
whose goals aligned with our own!

85
00:07:12.870 --> 00:07:17.240
Without them, Lord Oden's wish
will never come to pass!

86
00:07:21.830 --> 00:07:24.370
Pardon the intrusion! Pardon me!

87
00:07:24.370 --> 00:07:27.860
I was outside and couldn't help but overhear!

88
00:07:28.980 --> 00:07:31.280
You all have lovely voices!

89
00:07:31.280 --> 00:07:33.570
Hold it! Who are you?!

90
00:07:33.570 --> 00:07:34.840
Oh?

91
00:07:35.580 --> 00:07:39.310
Wow! What beauty! A goddess, no less!

92
00:07:40.460 --> 00:07:41.510
Oh, you!

93
00:07:41.510 --> 00:07:43.820
Please, come in.

94
00:07:43.820 --> 00:07:46.820
Oh, thank you kindly.

95
00:07:46.820 --> 00:07:47.520
Hey!

96
00:07:50.250 --> 00:07:51.370
As I live and breathe...

97
00:07:51.370 --> 00:07:54.080
Little Shinobu?!

98
00:07:56.540 --> 00:07:58.210
Young Kanjuro!

99
00:07:58.960 --> 00:08:03.270
Oh, I see, I see!

100
00:08:03.270 --> 00:08:07.580
Then what I have is
the genuine article, isn't it?!

101
00:08:07.580 --> 00:08:11.290
It's all anyone can talk about in the capital!

102
00:08:11.290 --> 00:08:14.170
I can't hold my excitement!

103
00:08:14.960 --> 00:08:19.100
Is it set to begin?! The great battle?!

104
00:08:20.850 --> 00:08:26.270
<b>The Northern
Ringo Cemetery</b>

105
00:08:36.170 --> 00:08:37.490
My sword...

106
00:08:37.490 --> 00:08:39.320
My sword!

107
00:08:44.490 --> 00:08:46.220
You're...

108
00:08:46.220 --> 00:08:48.970
You scared me!

109
00:08:49.510 --> 00:08:52.330
Please, do not move...

110
00:08:53.860 --> 00:08:55.720
It will aggravate your wound...

111
00:08:55.720 --> 00:08:59.210
She's right! You don't need to get up yet!

112
00:09:00.550 --> 00:09:02.400
Where am I?

113
00:09:09.110 --> 00:09:15.440
You saved our lives earlier.
Thank you so much.

114
00:09:18.070 --> 00:09:20.050
Thank you!

115
00:09:21.470 --> 00:09:24.490
But in result, you were terribly wounded!

116
00:09:25.030 --> 00:09:28.760
I am truly... at a loss as to how to apologize.

117
00:09:30.790 --> 00:09:33.970
It's my own fault I was hurt.

118
00:09:33.970 --> 00:09:36.140
You have nothing to apologize for...

119
00:09:37.960 --> 00:09:41.050
Where'd that guy go?!

120
00:09:41.050 --> 00:09:43.340
He still has Shusui!

121
00:09:43.770 --> 00:09:46.900
Please do not venture out with such an injury!

122
00:09:46.900 --> 00:09:48.210
That hurts!

123
00:09:48.210 --> 00:09:51.500
That's my wounded side, you idiot!

124
00:09:51.500 --> 00:09:52.520
I'm so sorry!

125
00:09:52.520 --> 00:09:54.320
Honestly...!

126
00:09:54.320 --> 00:09:55.980
See ya!

127
00:09:56.570 --> 00:10:00.320
Do not go! Your wound has not yet healed!

128
00:10:00.320 --> 00:10:01.980
Ow, ow, ow, ouch!

129
00:10:01.980 --> 00:10:05.080
I just told you that's my
wounded arm! Pay attention!

130
00:10:05.080 --> 00:10:06.840
I-I am so sorry!

131
00:10:10.020 --> 00:10:12.290
Ow, ow, ow...

132
00:10:12.290 --> 00:10:14.640
It'll be okay, Mr. Samurai!

133
00:10:14.640 --> 00:10:16.360
You'll get better soon!

134
00:10:16.360 --> 00:10:20.110
I stole this toad oil ointment in the capital...

135
00:10:20.720 --> 00:10:22.030
I mean, I bought it!

136
00:10:22.030 --> 00:10:23.510
You stole it.

137
00:10:23.510 --> 00:10:25.090
D-Did not.

138
00:10:26.370 --> 00:10:28.270
Well, I don't care either way.

139
00:10:28.270 --> 00:10:30.310
This toad oil is amazing!

140
00:10:30.940 --> 00:10:33.980
It makes sword cuts disappear!

141
00:10:33.980 --> 00:10:38.370
Toad oil, huh? Well, I hope it works!

142
00:10:40.330 --> 00:10:42.990
Hey, Mr. Samurai!

143
00:10:45.790 --> 00:10:47.580
Don't leave us!

144
00:10:50.520 --> 00:10:52.260
Got something to eat?

145
00:10:52.260 --> 00:10:54.790
Yes! Would you like some now?!

146
00:11:02.390 --> 00:11:03.420
Gyukimaru?

147
00:11:03.420 --> 00:11:05.540
Th-That's right.

148
00:11:07.110 --> 00:11:11.600
The whole city is familiar
with "Gyukimaru of Bandit's Bridge."

149
00:11:12.220 --> 00:11:17.400
The named blade Shusui has already
been returned to where it belongs.

150
00:11:17.400 --> 00:11:24.400
It's a treasure that was stolen from the grave
of the legendary samurai of Wano, Ryuma!

151
00:11:24.490 --> 00:11:27.350
It's unknown where he resides,

152
00:11:27.350 --> 00:11:32.710
but he'll confront any armed individual
who attempts to cross the bridge.

153
00:11:34.240 --> 00:11:39.080
Ah, so he's always there?
No need to rush then...

154
00:11:39.080 --> 00:11:42.420
I'm still curious about Gyukimaru,

155
00:11:42.420 --> 00:11:44.760
but first, who are you two?

156
00:11:44.760 --> 00:11:48.340
Why was that grim reaper-
looking guy after you?

157
00:11:57.470 --> 00:12:02.450
It's because we incurred the wrath
of the shogun of Wano.

158
00:12:02.450 --> 00:12:04.170
The shogun, huh?

159
00:12:04.170 --> 00:12:06.410
Oro... Oroshi?

160
00:12:06.410 --> 00:12:07.780
It's Orochi.

161
00:12:07.780 --> 00:12:10.330
Hey, Mr. Samurai!

162
00:12:11.220 --> 00:12:13.040
My name is Toko!

163
00:12:11.790 --> 00:12:16.410
<b>TOKO</b>

164
00:12:13.040 --> 00:12:16.410
If you use the "O" honorific,
you get "Otoko," and that means "man."

165
00:12:13.160 --> 00:12:16.410
<b>O</b>

166
00:12:17.590 --> 00:12:19.870
It's funny, right?!

167
00:12:19.870 --> 00:12:21.030
No, not really.

168
00:12:21.030 --> 00:12:22.960
What? What?!

169
00:12:23.750 --> 00:12:27.600
Everyone says it's funny!
Why don't you think so?!

170
00:12:27.600 --> 00:12:28.810
Beats me.

171
00:12:31.750 --> 00:12:35.560
Though you wear the garb
of a Wanese samurai,

172
00:12:35.560 --> 00:12:37.650
you are actually from overseas, correct?

173
00:12:37.650 --> 00:12:40.470
You don't look like a bad...

174
00:12:41.510 --> 00:12:42.490
A bad per...

175
00:12:44.150 --> 00:12:44.940
A bad person.

176
00:12:44.940 --> 00:12:46.990
Just say it!

177
00:12:46.200 --> 00:12:46.990
I apologize!

178
00:12:47.970 --> 00:12:50.690
Mr. Samurai, you're pretty scary!

179
00:12:50.690 --> 00:12:54.830
But you're a really nice person
because you saved us!

180
00:13:13.020 --> 00:13:13.760
Um...

181
00:13:15.160 --> 00:13:18.560
I wish to tell you a secret,
but you must promise to keep it.

182
00:13:21.650 --> 00:13:22.730
What is it?

183
00:13:22.730 --> 00:13:26.720
I'm... looking for my older brother.

184
00:13:26.720 --> 00:13:29.420
We were separated twenty years ago...

185
00:13:33.490 --> 00:13:37.380
And now, I think he might be in Wano!

186
00:13:38.130 --> 00:13:40.710
His name is...

187
00:13:40.710 --> 00:13:42.680
Kozuki Momonosuke.

188
00:13:44.140 --> 00:13:45.740
I'm his younger sister.

189
00:13:49.160 --> 00:13:50.920
My name is Hiyori!

190
00:13:55.460 --> 00:13:58.180
Momonosuke's younger sister?!

191
00:13:59.270 --> 00:14:00.230
I knew it!

192
00:14:00.230 --> 00:14:02.990
I'm so glad I summoned
the courage to tell you!

193
00:14:04.270 --> 00:14:06.160
I kind of took a chance.

194
00:14:07.520 --> 00:14:09.490
You do know my brother, don't you?!

195
00:14:10.180 --> 00:14:11.900
And he is okay, right?!

196
00:14:11.900 --> 00:14:14.130
Wait! Calm down!

197
00:14:14.130 --> 00:14:16.080
I need to collect my thoughts.

198
00:14:17.830 --> 00:14:21.480
Lately, rumors abound concerning
the return of the Kozuki Clan.

199
00:14:22.080 --> 00:14:27.540
Coincidentally, a strong, kindhearted
samurai from overseas is here.

200
00:14:27.540 --> 00:14:29.670
I thought he might be my brother's ally!

201
00:14:31.180 --> 00:14:34.900
Or are you an enemy
trying to track him down?!

202
00:14:34.900 --> 00:14:36.020
I'm his ally.

203
00:14:37.680 --> 00:14:39.320
I'm definitely his ally.

204
00:14:40.820 --> 00:14:42.360
I am so relieved.

205
00:14:44.110 --> 00:14:47.650
Do you know if Kin'emon is alive?

206
00:14:49.670 --> 00:14:54.750
Are Kanjuro, Raizo, and Kikunojo all with him?

207
00:14:54.750 --> 00:14:56.280
Kikunojo?

208
00:14:57.500 --> 00:14:59.240
Oh, you mean Kiku?

209
00:14:59.240 --> 00:15:03.470
Yeah, but wait... Something doesn't add up.

210
00:15:03.470 --> 00:15:06.250
Are you really Momo's sister?

211
00:15:09.280 --> 00:15:10.930
Let me explain.

212
00:15:13.880 --> 00:15:15.430
I see.

213
00:15:15.430 --> 00:15:17.510
That's right.

214
00:15:17.510 --> 00:15:21.400
Momo from twenty years ago
appears to be eight years old,

215
00:15:21.400 --> 00:15:24.690
and you're supposed to be his younger sister,

216
00:15:24.690 --> 00:15:27.360
but you aged twenty years
and you're now twenty-six...

217
00:15:27.360 --> 00:15:28.530
Yes.

218
00:15:28.530 --> 00:15:29.840
By the way...

219
00:15:31.080 --> 00:15:31.620
Huh?

220
00:15:32.040 --> 00:15:34.540
...is it okay for her to hear all of this?

221
00:15:35.020 --> 00:15:38.020
It's okay because I already knew!

222
00:15:40.080 --> 00:15:43.270
It was a secret between Big Sis and me!

223
00:15:43.270 --> 00:15:47.840
Otoko is one of the few close friends
who knows my true identity.

224
00:15:49.020 --> 00:15:53.170
Her cheerfulness sustains me day-to-day...

225
00:15:53.170 --> 00:15:58.560
Twenty years ago, I was
still a little girl like her...

226
00:15:59.810 --> 00:16:03.890
but I will never forget
what happened that day.

227
00:16:09.230 --> 00:16:12.240
You must escape... to the future!

228
00:16:14.580 --> 00:16:17.580
Mother, please don't do this!

229
00:16:17.580 --> 00:16:21.210
Mother! Mother!

230
00:16:23.760 --> 00:16:27.160
I couldn't make sense of
anything that was happening.

231
00:16:28.010 --> 00:16:30.590
In the blazing fire,

232
00:16:30.590 --> 00:16:35.210
my brother and the others
disappeared right before my eyes...

233
00:16:37.710 --> 00:16:40.850
It was the same day
I lost my father Oden,

234
00:16:40.850 --> 00:16:42.390
and even my mother...

235
00:16:42.960 --> 00:16:45.580
In a single day, I suddenly lost everything.

236
00:16:46.460 --> 00:16:49.800
I was told my brother
would return in twenty years...

237
00:16:50.460 --> 00:16:55.550
but for something so uncertain,
my hope was fleeting...

238
00:16:56.820 --> 00:17:00.660
I did not have the will to go on
for all those years.

239
00:17:02.020 --> 00:17:04.960
Why didn't you travel through time too?

240
00:17:05.580 --> 00:17:10.670
In case something happened
either to my brother or to me...

241
00:17:10.670 --> 00:17:13.840
they did not want the Kozuki bloodline to end.

242
00:17:13.840 --> 00:17:16.840
That's too cruel...

243
00:17:16.840 --> 00:17:20.430
But my father's retainer,

244
00:17:20.430 --> 00:17:26.270
Kawamatsu the Kappa, provided emotional
support and raised me with patience.

245
00:17:26.270 --> 00:17:27.230
A kappa?!

246
00:17:27.230 --> 00:17:28.610
Indeed.

247
00:17:28.610 --> 00:17:34.910
It is hard to believe such creatures exist,
but he takes great pride in being one.

248
00:17:35.860 --> 00:17:39.510
On the day that the castle burned,
we were surrounded by the enemy,

249
00:17:39.510 --> 00:17:44.410
but we escaped undetected
through a drainage channel in the moat.

250
00:17:44.410 --> 00:17:47.250
Princess! I ask for patience!

251
00:17:50.990 --> 00:17:54.630
After losing my father, mother, and brother,

252
00:17:54.630 --> 00:18:00.100
I couldn't speak from the shock of it all,
but he was always upbeat and supportive.

253
00:18:00.100 --> 00:18:03.380
Princess! This is the Kappa Dance!

254
00:18:03.380 --> 00:18:08.180
♪ Come on! Kappappa, kappappa, ♪
♪ kappappa and pa! ♪

255
00:18:08.180 --> 00:18:10.310
♪ Kappappa, kappappa... ♪

256
00:18:10.310 --> 00:18:13.950
Go ahead and eat, Princess.

257
00:18:18.600 --> 00:18:21.070
Kawamatsu, you're hungry too, aren't you?

258
00:18:21.070 --> 00:18:27.540
No, my tummy's upset.
That's why it's growling.

259
00:18:28.040 --> 00:18:32.260
Please... Please eat at least half.

260
00:18:32.260 --> 00:18:37.130
No, I'm fine. I found a grilled fish
swimming in the river earlier.

261
00:18:41.680 --> 00:18:43.560
A grilled fish in the river?

262
00:18:43.560 --> 00:18:44.640
That's right!

263
00:18:45.270 --> 00:18:50.310
So I filleted it real quick and ate it on the way.

264
00:18:51.780 --> 00:18:56.370
He did not eat much himself,
but he did his best to feed me.

265
00:18:57.240 --> 00:19:02.180
Due to the kindness
of my dutiful protector, Kawamatsu,

266
00:19:02.180 --> 00:19:05.240
I gradually learned to laugh again.

267
00:19:06.210 --> 00:19:07.910
Where's this guy now?

268
00:19:08.700 --> 00:19:12.570
I think when I was about thirteen,

269
00:19:12.570 --> 00:19:13.960
we were separated...

270
00:19:14.560 --> 00:19:19.600
But Kawamatsu is a strong samurai,

271
00:19:19.600 --> 00:19:24.840
so he must still be out there,
awaiting the day of the great battle!

272
00:19:25.570 --> 00:19:28.470
How I wish to see him and the others again...

273
00:19:28.470 --> 00:19:30.470
I wanna see a kappa too!

274
00:19:33.330 --> 00:19:34.300
Uh-huh!

275
00:19:35.210 --> 00:19:36.140
Zorojuro...

276
00:19:37.450 --> 00:19:42.400
Who else is preparing for the great battle?

277
00:19:42.400 --> 00:19:44.860
Well, let's see...

278
00:19:44.860 --> 00:19:46.670
What?!

279
00:19:46.670 --> 00:19:49.830
Then Doggy and Kitty are preparing too?!

280
00:19:49.830 --> 00:19:50.700
Yeah.

281
00:19:50.700 --> 00:19:56.160
I heard that they were both dead,
so I thought I would never see them again!

282
00:19:56.160 --> 00:20:00.600
Nekomamushi might not be in Wano yet...

283
00:20:04.010 --> 00:20:05.640
What are you doing?

284
00:20:05.640 --> 00:20:07.840
I am so, so happy...

285
00:20:14.230 --> 00:20:16.060
You crack me up, Big Sis!

286
00:20:20.470 --> 00:20:22.220
But I will not cry!

287
00:20:23.080 --> 00:20:25.280
I am the daughter of a samurai!

288
00:20:25.280 --> 00:20:28.270
If Doggy and Kitty will be there,

289
00:20:28.270 --> 00:20:32.670
then it's possible the entirety
of the Nine Red Scabbards will assemble!

290
00:20:32.670 --> 00:20:34.620
I'm not so sure of that.

291
00:20:34.620 --> 00:20:36.070
Kin'emon.

292
00:20:37.030 --> 00:20:38.360
Kanjuro.

293
00:20:39.350 --> 00:20:40.850
Raizo.

294
00:20:41.780 --> 00:20:43.510
Okiku.

295
00:20:44.360 --> 00:20:45.800
Inuarashi.

296
00:20:46.920 --> 00:20:48.390
Nekomamushi.

297
00:20:50.720 --> 00:20:58.980
<b>THE NINE RED SCABBARDS</b>

298
00:20:52.380 --> 00:20:57.360
All we know is those six and Momonosuke.

299
00:20:57.360 --> 00:21:00.950
We haven't met the last three yet.

300
00:21:00.950 --> 00:21:05.120
I spoke of the first
of those three, Kawamatsu,

301
00:21:03.700 --> 00:21:07.160
<b>KAWAMATSU</b>

302
00:21:03.700 --> 00:21:07.540
<b>DENJIRO</b>

303
00:21:04.080 --> 00:21:07.540
<b>ASHURA DOJI</b>

304
00:21:05.120 --> 00:21:07.540
and there's Denjiro and Ashura Doji.

305
00:21:07.540 --> 00:21:13.530
I do not know where they are
or if they are safe...

306
00:21:14.690 --> 00:21:19.420
But now, with everyone in the capital
in an uproar about this flyer...

307
00:21:19.420 --> 00:21:21.880
I just know they will appear!

308
00:21:21.880 --> 00:21:25.630
Is that the flyer we handed out to the rebels?

309
00:21:25.630 --> 00:21:26.960
Yes.

310
00:21:26.960 --> 00:21:33.050
Thanks to that uproar, the message has spread
very fast, which you'd think is a good thing,

311
00:21:33.050 --> 00:21:35.510
but it actually puts us in a tight spot...

312
00:21:35.510 --> 00:21:39.580
seeing as the rendezvous point
was compromised and our allies caught.

313
00:21:40.450 --> 00:21:42.940
Things are looking a bit dicey.

314
00:21:42.940 --> 00:21:44.690
It will be all right.

315
00:21:45.570 --> 00:21:48.070
That is my belief.

316
00:21:48.070 --> 00:21:48.650
Well...

317
00:21:51.700 --> 00:21:57.500
Too many captains sink the ship.
I'm gonna stop fretting.

318
00:21:57.500 --> 00:21:59.060
Oh, yes! Certainly!

319
00:21:59.060 --> 00:22:03.000
Before anything else, I want you to get well!

320
00:22:03.000 --> 00:22:05.360
Now, get some rest.

321
00:22:05.360 --> 00:22:07.810
Yeah, you don't have to tell me twice...

322
00:22:10.750 --> 00:22:12.490
Otoko, this is miracle!

323
00:22:12.490 --> 00:22:13.720
I am overjoyed!

324
00:22:14.800 --> 00:22:17.220
My brother is alive!

325
00:22:18.600 --> 00:22:20.850
I'm happy for you, Big Sis!

326
00:22:24.100 --> 00:22:26.410
I'm happy for you, Big Sis!

327
00:22:26.410 --> 00:22:27.980
Toko, this is great!

328
00:22:31.630 --> 00:22:35.160
Can't they keep it down?
So much for sleeping!

329
00:22:41.160 --> 00:22:42.710
But he is only eight!

330
00:22:42.710 --> 00:22:44.580
How peculiar.

331
00:22:45.110 --> 00:22:47.670
My brother is still a child.

332
00:22:47.670 --> 00:22:51.680
I suppose Kin'emon and the others
haven't changed in twenty years either.

333
00:22:51.680 --> 00:22:55.480
I cannot help but wonder
how our reunion will be.

334
00:22:55.480 --> 00:22:59.200
Perhaps it is better not to see them
before the great battle.

335
00:22:59.200 --> 00:23:03.650
I should not interfere in a samurai's struggle.

336
00:23:03.650 --> 00:23:05.440
Agreed, Otoko?

