<b>PRISON</b>

384
00:23:27.680 --> 00:23:28.720
<b>RASETSU            PRISON</b>

385
00:23:28.760 --> 00:23:34.020
<b>Prisoners' Quarters
AKA the Public Cells
Rasetsu Town</b>

386
00:23:29.780 --> 00:23:34.020
I didn't they'd have caught so many ruffians!

387
00:23:34.020 --> 00:23:38.220
People, take a good, long look at them!

388
00:23:38.220 --> 00:23:46.150
Take in the faces of fools who would rise up
against Shogun Orochi and Lord Kaido!

389
00:23:51.740 --> 00:23:53.490
Get your ass in there already!

390
00:23:58.930 --> 00:24:00.750
Too bad for you.

391
00:24:00.750 --> 00:24:04.080
You've been outed, your scheme revealed!

392
00:24:04.770 --> 00:24:06.540
You have failed.

393
00:24:06.540 --> 00:24:09.200
Sir Fukurokuju, please wait!

394
00:24:09.200 --> 00:24:13.340
What would lead you believe that this
ankle tattoo marks us as rebels?!

395
00:24:13.340 --> 00:24:17.800
This is just a popular design! We have
nothing to do with any kind of rebellion!

396
00:24:17.800 --> 00:24:22.510
Enough! What's your explanation
for this flyer, then?!

397
00:24:24.040 --> 00:24:28.510
With the reversed crescent moon at its center?

398
00:24:28.510 --> 00:24:33.980
A sign of rebellion against
Shogun Orochi, perhaps?

399
00:24:33.980 --> 00:24:37.160
It's a dead ringer for your tattoos.

400
00:24:37.720 --> 00:24:42.120
Shogun Orochi is the one giving
the order, so sit down and shut up!

401
00:24:54.060 --> 00:24:56.090
We're in a serious jam...

402
00:24:56.090 --> 00:24:58.300
Will everyone think...

403
00:24:59.960 --> 00:25:02.690
that we blabbed about the plan?

404
00:25:05.470 --> 00:25:06.560
Don't worry...

405
00:25:06.560 --> 00:25:10.900
Captain will continue to believe in us...

406
00:25:15.360 --> 00:25:17.860
<b>Prisoner Mining Camp

Udon</b>

407
00:25:26.670 --> 00:25:32.130
Come on, come on!
Wipe the floor with them already!

408
00:25:36.140 --> 00:25:38.920
I wish I could join a sumo match too...

409
00:25:38.920 --> 00:25:45.520
I'm Madilloman! A Gifter who ate
the Armadillo SMILE Fruit!

410
00:25:42.730 --> 00:25:46.640
<b>Madilloman 
 A Gifter 
Armadillo SMILE Fruit</b>

411
00:25:50.110 --> 00:25:53.260
Oh, you look like you have tough body!

412
00:25:53.260 --> 00:25:54.740
Perfect for my training!

413
00:25:54.740 --> 00:25:56.190
You moron!

414
00:25:56.190 --> 00:26:00.750
I'm rockin' seastone bullets in these bad boys!

415
00:26:03.360 --> 00:26:05.910
You're finished, fellas!

416
00:26:07.490 --> 00:26:09.130
They're "finished"?

417
00:26:09.130 --> 00:26:14.750
How blind are these idiots?!
It's far from "finished."

418
00:26:16.270 --> 00:26:17.180
Gramps!

419
00:26:17.180 --> 00:26:20.210
Go right, duck, and then jump.

420
00:26:20.210 --> 00:26:20.920
Huh?!

421
00:26:20.920 --> 00:26:22.140
Get dead!

422
00:26:22.140 --> 00:26:22.940
Run!

423
00:26:22.940 --> 00:26:23.800
Okay!

424
00:26:24.800 --> 00:26:26.260
"Go right"!

425
00:26:27.220 --> 00:26:28.220
"Duck"!

426
00:26:28.220 --> 00:26:30.400
And...

427
00:26:29.600 --> 00:26:30.390
You little...!

428
00:26:30.400 --> 00:26:31.560
..."jump"!

429
00:26:39.620 --> 00:26:41.820
– Whaaat?!
– Whaaat?!

430
00:26:41.820 --> 00:26:43.820
Ow, ow, ow...

431
00:26:44.910 --> 00:26:46.790
Damn, damn, damn, damn, damn, damn!

432
00:26:48.840 --> 00:26:51.040
Good job, gramps! Keep it up!

433
00:26:51.040 --> 00:26:55.420
What the...?! Are you able
to peek into the future?

434
00:26:55.420 --> 00:26:56.760
Screw you!

435
00:26:56.760 --> 00:27:01.670
That's pure nonsense!
What'd you actually do?!

436
00:27:08.310 --> 00:27:10.190
Gramps! Go left next!

437
00:27:10.190 --> 00:27:10.940
What?!

438
00:27:10.940 --> 00:27:12.560
Why, you...!

439
00:27:12.560 --> 00:27:14.140
"Left"!

440
00:27:15.530 --> 00:27:18.310
Dammit, that geezer!

441
00:27:18.310 --> 00:27:19.610
Try this on for size!

442
00:27:24.500 --> 00:27:27.620
"Left"! "Left"! "Left"! "Left"!

443
00:27:30.890 --> 00:27:32.130
You little cheat!

444
00:27:36.090 --> 00:27:37.220
Bull's-eye!

445
00:27:44.450 --> 00:27:46.560
Guns can't take me down!

446
00:27:47.890 --> 00:27:50.690
Y-You sneaky little...!

447
00:27:58.580 --> 00:28:01.280
It's not over yet!

448
00:28:01.950 --> 00:28:04.080
Send him flying without making contact!

449
00:28:10.580 --> 00:28:11.890
That's not it.

450
00:28:11.890 --> 00:28:13.910
That's just the normal armament...

451
00:28:17.130 --> 00:28:18.970
Oh, crap!

452
00:28:20.010 --> 00:28:21.920
Armadi-Guard!

453
00:28:25.930 --> 00:28:26.980
This isn't it...

454
00:28:26.980 --> 00:28:29.970
This is still just the normal armament...

455
00:28:29.970 --> 00:28:32.240
Huh?! Weren't you gonna hit me?!

456
00:28:33.930 --> 00:28:37.010
Alpaca Fencing!

457
00:28:37.010 --> 00:28:39.690
Hey! Which way next?!

458
00:28:39.690 --> 00:28:43.070
Sir Straw Hat!

459
00:28:43.070 --> 00:28:45.160
Alright! Stop right there!

460
00:28:45.160 --> 00:28:46.440
This good?!

461
00:28:51.350 --> 00:28:53.200
It'll be easier this way!

462
00:28:53.200 --> 00:28:55.120
I'm so sorry...!

463
00:28:55.120 --> 00:28:57.230
Ready when you are, Alpacaman!

464
00:28:57.230 --> 00:28:58.360
Bring it!

465
00:28:59.710 --> 00:29:05.060
Put me down! It's not right
for me to burden you this way!

466
00:29:06.160 --> 00:29:09.510
Nope. Actually, the heavier the better.

467
00:29:09.510 --> 00:29:10.680
What?!

468
00:29:15.360 --> 00:29:17.100
It's good for my training!

469
00:29:22.420 --> 00:29:24.690
I see, I see...!

470
00:29:26.450 --> 00:29:32.530
This flyer told us all we needed
to know of the upcoming battle!

471
00:29:32.530 --> 00:29:38.260
Two birds on fire... That means twilight
on the day of the Fire Festival!

472
00:29:38.260 --> 00:29:42.540
The rendezvous point for the raid is Habu Port!

473
00:29:43.190 --> 00:29:46.810
Young Kin'emon must've put his brain
into overtime for this.

474
00:29:47.650 --> 00:29:49.840
Young... Kin'emon?

475
00:29:50.760 --> 00:29:53.750
Oh, why are you giving me that look,

476
00:29:53.750 --> 00:29:55.270
Little Shinobu?!

477
00:29:57.420 --> 00:30:01.950
So, that's how things are. The dejected
looks on your faces make total sense.

478
00:30:01.950 --> 00:30:05.010
The plan's as good as ruined,

479
00:30:05.010 --> 00:30:07.990
what with our enemies aware of it.

480
00:30:08.760 --> 00:30:11.740
Mm-hmm. That is correct...

481
00:30:12.260 --> 00:30:16.370
Allies who bear the reversed crescent
moon tattoo—the sign of our rebellion—

482
00:30:16.370 --> 00:30:18.710
are getting rounded up now.

483
00:30:21.070 --> 00:30:25.550
If only there was some way
to take it back and tell them, "It was all fake!"

484
00:30:25.550 --> 00:30:29.090
But that would mislead your allies as well.

485
00:30:30.380 --> 00:30:35.690
Before this, however, I didn't know about
the crescent moon ankle tattoo.

486
00:30:35.690 --> 00:30:38.510
It brought in allies like myself.

487
00:30:52.460 --> 00:30:55.240
That wasn't it! I can't do it right!

488
00:30:55.240 --> 00:30:56.420
What?!

489
00:30:57.380 --> 00:31:02.280
This whole time, when you hit
a foe you say, "That wasn't it"!

490
00:31:02.280 --> 00:31:04.130
What are you trying to do?

491
00:31:04.130 --> 00:31:07.790
I wanna send enemies flying with a punch
that doesn't even touch them!

492
00:31:07.790 --> 00:31:09.810
If I do that...

493
00:31:09.810 --> 00:31:14.020
I think I can break through
Kaido's tough scales!

494
00:31:14.020 --> 00:31:16.770
Send enemies flying with
a punch that doesn't touch...

495
00:31:16.770 --> 00:31:20.600
Yeah. I won't know if it works
until I actually do it.

496
00:31:20.600 --> 00:31:23.100
The thing is, I've seen it before...

497
00:31:24.000 --> 00:31:25.030
Both Rayleigh...

498
00:31:27.000 --> 00:31:29.360
and that battle-axe guy...

499
00:31:30.490 --> 00:31:32.940
used the same armament haki.

500
00:31:32.940 --> 00:31:35.210
How is theirs different from mine?!

501
00:31:35.210 --> 00:31:38.170
Haki must be a foreign concept.

502
00:31:38.170 --> 00:31:40.210
You know something?!

503
00:31:40.210 --> 00:31:45.170
In Wano, we utilize an invisible power that
stems from the body and covers one's blade.

504
00:31:46.080 --> 00:31:49.290
A good sword will cut even iron
when you need it to,

505
00:31:49.290 --> 00:31:52.390
and when you don't, it won't
even nick a sheet of paper.

506
00:31:52.390 --> 00:31:55.100
It's at the swordsman's discretion!

507
00:32:06.020 --> 00:32:07.490
Gramps...!

508
00:32:07.490 --> 00:32:10.360
Check out this geezer!
Ready for us to end you?!

509
00:32:11.320 --> 00:32:13.520
Sir Straw Hat.

510
00:32:13.520 --> 00:32:18.810
Watch as I demonstrate the power honed
through my days of sword fighting.

511
00:32:24.980 --> 00:32:29.520
Despite being the centerpiece
of a sick execution game,

512
00:32:29.520 --> 00:32:33.840
he's using it as a training opportunity?!

513
00:32:35.300 --> 00:32:37.690
Sir Straw Hat! Give me directions!

514
00:32:38.610 --> 00:32:39.300
Okay!

515
00:32:46.920 --> 00:32:49.570
He'll swing down his right sword, full force!

516
00:32:50.310 --> 00:32:51.990
I got it!

517
00:33:06.080 --> 00:33:08.620
Damn you, geezer!

518
00:33:36.700 --> 00:33:38.250
He knocked him back!

519
00:33:46.080 --> 00:33:47.170
Gramps...

520
00:33:47.920 --> 00:33:52.120
Old man Hyo dropped that Gifter!

521
00:33:52.120 --> 00:33:53.510
Alpacaman!

522
00:33:56.530 --> 00:34:01.940
That old weakling... I swear
he had one foot in the grave.

523
00:34:01.940 --> 00:34:05.060
But he's surprisingly spry!

524
00:34:07.680 --> 00:34:09.900
Could old man Hyo actually be

525
00:34:09.900 --> 00:34:12.610
the renowned Hyogoro the Flower?!

526
